*12 (CommentText
uid 975,0
shape (Rectangle
uid 976,0
layer 0
va (VaSet
vasetType 1
fg "65280,65280,46080"
lineColor "0,0,32768"
)
xt "24000,33000,44000,39000"
)
oxt "0,0,15000,5000"
text (MLText
uid 977,0
va (VaSet
fg "0,0,32768"
)
xt "24200,33200,43800,38200"
st "
This indicates an early falling edge, signaling noise. The SyncHigh should only be 150 cycles but is sometimes up to 213. Thus the SyncHigh needs to be checked on its own. It seems to be a bus driver/transformer issue.

"
tm "CommentText"
wrapOption 3
visibleHeight 6000
visibleWidth 20000
)
)
*13 (CommentText
uid 988,0
shape (Rectangle
uid 989,0
layer 0
va (VaSet
vasetType 1
fg "59904,39936,65280"
lineColor "0,0,32768"
)
xt "25000,4000,41000,9000"
)
oxt "0,0,15000,5000"
text (MLText
uid 990,0
va (VaSet
fg "0,0,32768"
)
xt "25200,4200,41100,9200"
st "
This indicates a late falling edge, signaling invalid data, possibly noise. The limit is set to be 1500ns - 250ns allowed early pulse.
This could break physical implementation.
"
tm "CommentText"
wrapOption 3
visibleHeight 5000
visibleWidth 16000
)
)
